    "body": "We only send header requests to the peer we've chosen (the one with highest TD) to sync with. Once we have a batch of headers we'll request body parts for subsets of them to all available peers\r\n\r\nIf other peers manage to guess the headers we're expecting at any point in time and send them before the peer we're syncing with, then yeah, what you describe could happen, but these would still have to be validated before being inserted in our chain.\r\n\r\nAlso, I'm not sure I understand how that relates to the traceback here",
